President Uhuru Kenyatta has pledged Sh100 million to Kibabii University in Bungoma County for refurbishment. The President who is the Chancellor of the university on Friday held a meeting with the council and management of Kibabii University where he promised the institution the funding to support its ongoing upgrades of programmes and infrastructure. Read:Kibabii university closed indefinitely after students riot over seats, lecturers Uhuru said the Government will support the university to equip a laboratory and to improve the institution’s water supply. Council chairman, Dr Ernest Mwangi, and the Vice-Chancellor, Prof Isaac Odeo, led the delegation. They told the President that all programmes in the university were running well and the expansion of infrastructure was on course. Read:Kibabii University closed after riots over student election campaigns  Click here for the latest political news  